The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing in generating distractors for multiple-choice concept inventories, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the process. The concept inventories are related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and digital logic (cs.CE), which are both subfields of computer science. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in analyzing the open-ended responses collected from Amazon Mechanical Turk.
